GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 1
SENATE BILL 951
Short Title: Critical Funds for North Mecklenburg. (Public)
Sponsors: Senator Mohammed (Primary Sponsor).
Referred to: Rules and Operations of the Senate
May 4, 2026
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FUNDS FOR CRITICAL FUNDS FOR NORTH MECKLENBURG.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
5 Budget and Management the sum of twenty million four hundred forty thousand dollars
6 ($20,440,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to
7 the Town of Davidson for emergency services. These funds shall be used as follows:
8 (1) Seventeen million dollars ($17,000,000) for the construction of a fire station.
9 (2) Three million dollars ($3,000,000) to purchase an emergency vehicle.
10 (3) One hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) to purchase police equipment to
11 enhance community safety.
12 (4) Three hundred forty thousand dollars ($340,000) to replace breathing
13 apparatus equipment.
14 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
15 Budget and Management the sum of ten million dollars ($10,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for
16 the 2026-2027 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to the Town of Cornelius for the following
17 purposes and in the following amounts:
18 (1) Three million dollars ($3,000,000) for the acquisition of property for the
19 construction of a future public safety facility, including a future fire station
20 that will provide for emergency services for the southwest portion of the Town
21 and space for a police facility to augment current police space.
22 (2) One million five hundred thousand dollars ($1,500,000) for the replacement
23 of a fire engine.
24 (3) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) to improve pedestrian safety at the
25 intersection of NC 115 and Catawba Avenue to accommodate increased
26 pedestrian activity in the downtown Cornelius area.
27 (4) Three million five hundred thousand dollars ($3,500,000) to construct a
28 recreation center on the campus of an elementary school in the Town.
29 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of State
30 Budget and Management the sum of four million dollars ($4,000,000) in nonrecurring funds for
31 the 2026-2027 fiscal year to provide a directed grant to the Lake Norman Community
32 Development Corporation (Corporation), a nonprofit corporation, for the purposes and in the
33 amounts provided in this section. The Corporation may retain and use up to three percent (3%)
34 of the funds appropriated in this section for administrative expenses.
35 (1) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) for the development of affordable housing
36 throughout the Town of Cornelius, other than in the Smithville community.
*S951-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (2) Two million dollars ($2,000,000) for the acquisition of land and the
2 development of affordable housing in the Smithville community located in the
3 Town of Cornelius.
4 SECTION 4. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
